Micronutrient fertilization would be needed if you observe any deficiency symptoms or if soil pH is higher than 6.2. If nutrients levels are low, apply pre-planting fifty pounds per acre of N, 22 lb P/acre, and 41 lb K/acre using a fertilizer in granular form (500 lb/ac formula 10-10-10 or a similar one) and the rest of N via fertigation. On surface or trickle irrigated field apply 100 lb/acre of N at pre-planting and after first harvesting.
